(1) **Norms for establishing Service Companies of Lloyd’s India** The eligible promoters as mentioned in regulation 3(12) who wish to participate in Lloyd’s India shall set up a service company with the following norms: 

   - (a) The service company may be a private or a public limited company with a Paid up capital of rupees five lakh and is registered under the Indian Companies Act, 2013; 

   - (b) The main objects in the Memorandum of Association shall be to provide all technical, underwriting, binding risks, settling claims, administrative, accounting, investment, regulatory and other assistance to the syndicate whom they represent; 

      - _Provided that_ the Authority may specify such other main objects that may be specified in the MOA/AOA of the service company; 

   - (c) The service company shall be responsible for all statutory & regulatory filing and compliances on behalf of the syndicate it represents; 

